# Documentation Style Guide

Standards for documentation in this project.

## Markdown Best Practices

### Headers

Use ATX-style headers:

```markdown
# H1 - Page Title
## H2 - Major Section
### H3 - Subsection
```

### Code Blocks

Always specify language:

````markdown
```typescript
const example = "like this";
```
````

### Lists

**Unordered lists**: Use `-` (dash)

```markdown
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Nested item
```

**Ordered lists**: Use numbers

```markdown
1. First
2. Second
3. Third
```

**Task lists**:

```markdown
- [ ] Todo item
- [x] Completed item
```

### Links

**Internal**: Relative paths

```markdown
[See reference](../reference/plan_act.md)
```

**External**: Full URLs

```markdown
[Anthropic Skills](https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-skills)
```

## YAML Frontmatter

For discoverable resources (skills, personas, plans):

```yaml
---
name: resource-name
description: Complete description including WHEN to use
type: skill|persona|plan
---
```

### Required Fields

- `name`: hyphen-case, max 64 chars
- `description`: Complete, includes context

### Optional Fields

- `author`: Creator identifier
- `created`: Date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- `status`: draft|in-progress|completed
- `type`: Resource type

## Writing Style

### Imperative Form

Use imperative/infinitive voice:

✅ **Good**: "Create a file"  
❌ **Bad**: "Creates a file" or "Creating a file"

### Be Specific

✅ **Good**: "Run `npm test` to verify"  
❌ **Bad**: "Test the code"

### Provide Examples

Always include concrete examples:

```markdown
## Usage

```bash
npm run command --arg value
```

**Output**:
```
Success message
```
```

## Document Structure

### Skill Documentation (SKILL.md)

```markdown
---
name: skill-name
description: Complete description including when to use
---

# Skill Name

Brief overview.

## What It Does

Clear explanation.

## Usage

Step-by-step instructions with examples.

## Requirements

Dependencies and prerequisites.

## Troubleshooting

Common issues and solutions.
```

### Reference Documentation

```markdown
# Topic Name

Overview of the topic.

## Section 1

Content with examples.

## Section 2

More content.

## Best Practices

Actionable guidelines.
```

### Plan Documentation

```markdown
---
title: Plan Title
created: YYYY-MM-DD
status: draft
---

# Plan: Title

## Objective

Clear goal.

## Implementation Plan

### Phase 1
- [ ] Task 1
- [ ] Task 2

## Test Strategy

How to verify success.
```

## Length Guidelines

- **SKILL.md**: <500 lines (split to references/ if longer)
- **README.md**: <200 lines (link to deep docs)
- **AGENTS.md**: <300 lines (progressive disclosure)

## Formatting

### Tables

```markdown
| Column 1 | Column 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Value 1  | Value 2  |
```

### Callouts

Use standard markdown:

```markdown
**Note**: Important information

**Warning**: Potential issue

**Tip**: Helpful suggestion
```

## File Naming

- **Documentation**: `topic-name.md`
- **Templates**: `file-name.template`
- **Skills**: Match directory name

## Progressive Disclosure

Keep top-level concise, link to details:

```markdown
## Feature Name

Brief overview. [See detailed guide](./reference/feature-guide.md)
```

